2500|$|Father Federico Lombardi, a Vatican spokesman, {{claimed the}} Pope had not wished {{specifically}} to attack people with homosexual inclinations, {{and had not}} mentioned <b>gays</b> <b>or</b> <b>lesbians</b> in his text. Father Lombardi insisted, however, {{that there had been}} an overreaction to the Pope's remarks: [...] "He was speaking more generally about gender theories which overlook the fundamental difference in creation between men and women and focus instead on cultural conditioning." [...] Nevertheless, the remarks were interpreted as a call to save mankind from homosexuals and transsexuals.|$|R
